@PatriotFrontUpdates ¬ª Activists, during 2023, completed a total of 7,334 instances of activism, averaging 20 per day, in 47 states and the District of Columbia. Patriot Front held large marches in Austin, Columbus, and Washington, as well as almost a dozen protests of homosexual "drag" events in WY, TX, OH, TN and more. The organization provided a helping hand in disaster relief efforts after floods in Vermont, tornadoes in Tennessee, Arkansas, and Mississippi, and the chemical spill in East Palestine, Ohio. In addition, PF hosted numerous family-friendly social events and community projects around the country offering members and supporters a chance for fellowship and networking. Promat (red dots) was placed a total of 6,353 times in 2,167 cities, and all other forms of activism (gold triangles) constitute 981 collective instances. Each instance of promat, stencil, banner, and sign activism is composed of at least four individual placements in a single town.
